        <h2 id="faq">Frequently asked questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Are free social media schedulers actually free forever?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes — Buffer, Later, Publer, Meta Business Suite, and Canva all have free plans with no time limit. The catch is post caps (10–30/month), channel limits (1–3 accounts), and missing analytics. They are real tools, not trials, but you outgrow them once you ship more than a post a day across two platforms.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Which free scheduler supports the most platforms?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Publer covers the most major platforms on its free plan — Facebook, Instagram, Twitter/X, LinkedIn, GBP, Pinterest, and YouTube. Buffer covers 3 channels on free. Meta Business Suite only schedules Facebook + Instagram. Pallyy is Instagram-first but adds LinkedIn and TikTok on free.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Can I schedule Google Business Profile posts for free?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Publer's free plan is the cheapest path — it includes GBP scheduling on the free tier. Buffer and Later require paid plans for GBP. The theStacc Local SEO module ($49/mo) goes further by writing, designing, and auto-publishing GBP posts weekly.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the catch with free social media scheduling tools?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Three catches. First, post caps — most free plans stop at 10–30 scheduled posts a month. Second, analytics are stripped down to last-7-days only. Third, you can only connect 1–3 social accounts. Free works for testing or solo brands. For volume, you need a paid plan or a done-for-you service.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Should I use a free scheduler or just post manually?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>A free scheduler is worth it if you post more than twice a week on more than one platform. Below that, native posting is fine. Above that, batching a week of content in one sitting saves 3–5 hours a week — even on a free plan.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Which free scheduler has the best analytics?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Metricool wins on free analytics — 30 days of historical data across multiple channels, plus competitor tracking. Buffer free shows basic engagement only. Later free shows posts but not deep insights. For real reporting at zero cost, Metricool is the best pick.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Is there a free open-source social scheduler?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes — Postiz is fully open source and self-hostable. If you have the technical skill to deploy it on a VPS, you get unlimited posts, unlimited channels, and full control. The trade-off is setup time and ongoing maintenance you would not pay for with Buffer or Publer.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

